        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23553",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To make it completely clear:\n\nI have general Log class (writers - Db, Firebug) used in webapp. And I need to run some cron import scripts which should report errors in the Log.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-20T12:41:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-20T12:41:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23556",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What should likely happen is that if the response object is null, the channel writer should not attempt to instantiate the plugin.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-20T13:08:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-20T13:08:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Scheduling for RC3; Christoph, please see my previous comment for a solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-22T15:02:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-22T15:02:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I can fix the error described, however the intent is to throw an exception if the response object is not initialized to make it clear to the developer that the logged data will not make it into the response likely due to improper initialization. This is the intended behavior for WEB apps.\n\nWe have several options to solve this issue:\n\n1) Make it the developer's responsibility to disable the Zend_Wildfire_Plugin_FirePhp component when running in CLI mode\n{code}\nZend_Wildfire_Plugin_FirePhp::getInstance()->setEnabled(false);\n{code}\n\n2) Automatically disable the Zend_Wildfire_Plugin_FirePhp component when running in CLI mode\n\n3) Removing the exception altogether to not provide any feedback if the Zend_Wildfire_Plugin_FirePhp component is not properly initialized.\n\nMy preference would be option 2.\n\nAny comments?\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-24T00:01:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-24T00:01:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23648",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "(2) sounds good to me as well. However, how do you plan on determining that you're running from the CLI?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-24T13:32:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-24T13:32:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23649",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was hoping there was a ZF component for that, but I guess not.\n\nHow about\n\n{code}\n(php_sapi_name()=='cli')\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-24T13:50:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-24T13:50:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23684",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Log_Writer_Firebug is now disabled by default when run from the command line.\n\nIf you want to enable it you must use:\n\n{code}\n$writer = new Zend_Log_Writer_Firebug();\n$writer->setEnabled(true);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cadorn",
                        "name": "cadorn",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Dorn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-24T17:47:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-24T17:47:20.000+0000"
                },
